# Backend Patterns

## Response format
All routes must return ApiResponse<T> from src/types/index.ts.
Success: { success: true, data: T }
Error: { success: false, error: string }
Never return raw objects. Never return arrays directly.

## Error handling
Always use AppError from src/types/index.ts.
All route handlers must call next(err) — never catch and swallow.
Never use console.log. Use next(new AppError(message, statusCode)).
The errorHandler middleware in src/middleware/errorHandler.ts handles all errors.

## Validation
Every POST and PATCH route must apply the validate middleware before the handler.
Validate using the schema pattern already in src/middleware/validate.ts.

## Services
Service functions are async and return the data type directly (not wrapped).
Routes wrap the return value in ApiResponse<T>.
Services throw AppError on business logic failures.

## Naming
Routes: kebab-case filenames (tasks.ts, auth.ts)
Services: camelCase functions (createTask, findTaskById)
DTOs: PascalCase + suffix (CreateTaskDto, UpdateTaskDto)
